item.title: Python Basics for Data Analysis
item.description: Using Python to examine datasets (Basics) library(reticulate) library(tidyverse) ## -- Attaching packages ---------------------------- tidyverse 1.2.1 -- ## v ggplot2 3.2.1 v purrr 0.3.2 ## v tibble 2.1.3 v dplyr 0.8.3 ## v tidyr 1.0.0 v stringr 1.4.0 ## v readr 1.3.1 v forcats 0.4.0 ## -- Conflicts ------------------------------- tidyverse_conflicts() -- ## x dplyr::filter() masks stats::filter() ## x dplyr::lag() masks stats::lag() faithful<-faithful glimpse(faithful) ## Observations: 272 ## Variables: 2 ## $ eruptions <dbl> 3.
